senses
  entry
    definition "belonging to or on behalf of a specified person (especially yourself); preceded by a possessive"
    examples ("for your own use" "do your own thing" "she makes her own clothes" "‘ain’ is Scottish")
    id oewn-01773236-s
    partOfSpeech s
    synonyms (ain)
  entry
    definition "have ownership or possession of"
    examples ("He owns three houses in Florida" "How many cars does she have?")
    id oewn-02209474-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (have possess)
source "oewn:2024"
